GrpHdr: Set of characteristics shared by all individual transactions included in the message.
GrpHdr.MsgId:
Definition: Point to point reference, as assigned by the instructing party, and sent to the next party in the chain to unambiguously identify the message.
Usage: The instructing party has to make sure that MessageIdentification is unique per instructed party for a pre-agreed period.
GrpHdr.CreDtTm: Date and time at which the message was created.
TxInfAndSts: Information concerning the original transactions, to which the status report message refers.
TxInfAndSts.ExctnConf: Unique reference, as assigned by the account servicing institution, to unambiguously identify the confirmation.
TxInfAndSts.PrcgDt: Date/time at which the instruction was processed by the specified party.
TxInfAndSts.TxSts: Specifies the status of the transaction.
TxInfAndSts.StsId: Unique identification, as assigned by the original sending party, to unambiguously identify the status report.
TxInfAndSts.OrgnlInstrId:
Unique identification, as assigned by the original sending party, to
unambiguously identify the original instruction.

(FSPIOP equivalent: transactionRequestId)
TxInfAndSts.OrgnlEndToEndId:
Unique identification, as assigned by the original sending party, to
unambiguously identify the original end-to-end transaction.

(FSPIOP equivalent: transactionId)
TxInfAndSts.OrgnlTxId:
Unique identification, as assigned by the original sending party, to
unambiguously identify the original transaction.

(FSPIOP equivalent: quoteId)
TxInfAndSts.OrgnlUETR: Unique end-to-end transaction reference, as assigned by the original sending party, to unambiguously identify the original transaction.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf: Information concerning the reason for the status.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.Nm: Name by which a party is known and which is usually used to identify that party.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr: Information that locates and identifies a specific address, as defined by postal services.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.AdrT: Type of address, as defined by the postal services.
Type of address expressed as a code.
Type of address expressed as a proprietary code.
Proprietary information, often a code, issued by the data source scheme issuer.
Short textual description of the scheme.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.Care: Name of the person or entity the mail is directed to, if different from the recipient.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.Dept: Name of a department within an organization.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.SubD: Name of a sub-department within a department.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.Strt: Name of the street or thoroughfare.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.Bldg: Number that identifies a building on the street.
Name of the building, if applicable.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.Flr: Floor number or identifier within a building.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.Unit: Unit or apartment number within a building.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.Room: Room number or identifier within a building.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.TwnN: Name of the town or city.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.TwnL: Name of the location within a town or city.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.Dstr: Name of the district or region.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.Ctry: Name of the country subdivision, such as a state or province.
Country code, as defined by ISO 3166-1 alpha-2.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.PstlAdr.AdrL: Free-form text line for the address.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.Id: Unique and unambiguous identification of a party.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.Id.OrgId: Unique and unambiguous way to identify an organisation.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.Id.OrgId.Any: Business identification code of the organisation.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.Id.OrgId.LEI: Legal entity identification as an alternate identification for a party.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.Id.OrgId.Oth: Unique identification of an organisation, as assigned by an institution, using an identification scheme.
Name of the identification scheme, in a coded form as published in an external list.
Name of the identification scheme, in a free text form.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.Id.PrvtId: Unique and unambiguous identification of a person, for example a passport.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.Id.PrvtId.Dt: Date and place of birth of a person.
Date on which a person was born.
Province where a person was born.
City where a person was born.
Country where a person was born.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.Id.PrvtId.Ot: Unique identification of a person, as assigned by an institution, using an identification scheme.
Unique and unambiguous identification of a person.
Name of the identification scheme, in a coded form as published in an external list.
Name of the identification scheme, in a free text form.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtryOfRes:
Country of Residence
Country in which a person resides (the place of a person's home). In the case of a company, it is the country from which the affairs of that company are directed.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtctDtls: Set of elements used to indicate how to contact the party.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtctDtls.NmP: Specifies the terms used to formally address a person.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtctDtls.Nm: Name by which a party is known and which is usually used to identify that party.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtctDtls.Phn: Collection of information that identifies a phone number, as defined by telecom services.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtctDtls.Mob: Collection of information that identifies a mobile phone number, as defined by telecom services.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtctDtls.Fax: Collection of information that identifies a fax number, as defined by telecom services.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtctDtls.URL: Address for the Universal Resource Locator (URL), for example an address used over the www (HTTP) service.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtctDtls.Ema: Purpose for which an email address may be used.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtctDtls.Rsp: Role of a person in an organisation.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtctDtls.Dep: Identification of a division of a large organisation or building.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtctDtls.Oth: Method used to contact the financial institution's contact for the specific tax region.
Communication value such as phone number or email address.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Orgtr.CtctDtls.Pre: Preferred method used to reach the contact.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Rsn: Specifies the reason for the status report.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Rsn.Cd: Reason for the status, as published in an external reason code list.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.Rsn.Prtry: Reason for the status, in a proprietary form.
TxInfAndSts.StsRsnInf.AddtlInf: Additional information about the status report.
TxInfAndSts.AccptncDtTm: Date and time at which the status was accepted.
TxInfAndSts.AcctSvcrRef: Unique reference, as assigned by the account servicing institution, to unambiguously identify the status report.
TxInfAndSts.ClrSysRef: Reference that is assigned by the account servicing institution and sent to the account owner to unambiguously identify the transaction.
TxInfAndSts.SplmtryData: Additional information that cannot be captured in the structured elements and/or any other specific block.
TxInfAndSts.SplmtryData.PlcAndNm: Unambiguous reference to the location where the supplementary data must be inserted in the message instance.
TxInfAndSts.SplmtryData.Envlp:
Technical element wrapping the supplementary data.
Technical component that contains the validated supplementary data information. This technical envelope allows to segregate the supplementary data information from any other information.
